This paper is primarily focused on the performance analysis of vehicular communication systems, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a novel data-driven approach using machine learning models, which suggests a potential fit for the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of the system, which could be categorized under control systems (cs.SY) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper also mentions security and privacy concerns, which could be classified under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
